"{\"abstract\":\"In this paper, we present a learning-based framework for light field view synthesis from a subset of input views. Building upon a light-weight optical flow estimation network to obtain depth maps, our method employs two reconstruction modules in pixel and feature domains respectively. For the pixel-wise reconstruction, occlusions are explicitly handled by a disparity-dependent interpolation filter, whereas inpainting on disoccluded areas is learned by convolutional layers. Due to disparity inconsistencies, the pixel-based reconstruction may lead to blurriness in highly textured areas as well as on object contours. On the contrary, the feature-based reconstruction well performs on high frequencies, making the reconstruction in the two domains complementary. End-to-end learning is finally performed including a fusion module merging pixel and feature-based reconstructions. Experimental results show that our method achieves state-of-the-art performance on both synthetic and real-world datasets, moreover, it is even able to extend light fields' baseline by extrapolating high quality views without additional training.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"11858101\",\"name\":\"Jinglei Shi\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/11858101\"},{\"authorId\":\"1926478\",\"name\":\"Xiaoran Jiang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1926478\"},{\"authorId\":\"1780587\",\"name\":\"C. Guillemot\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1780587\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"2007.02252\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2861519\",\"name\":\"Gaochang Wu\"},{\"authorId\":\"1680777\",\"name\":\"Yebin Liu\"},{\"authorId\":\"152599430\",\"name\":\"Lu Fang\"},{\"authorId\":\"145011553\",\"name\":\"T. Chai\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\",\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"b379814da3eba677e51fda11f4874964e74f8f16\",\"title\":\"Spatial-Angular Attention Network for Light Field 